<br>
In RvR, when I'm fighting a fully buffed Healer (who is Thrust Vulnerable), I MIGHT be lucky and see a 200 dmg hit on my mainhand, out of a potential damage cap of 300+.<br>
<br>
A Berserker using Slash OR Crush against my Chain will hit me for approx 400 dmg mainhand out of a potential cap of 500ish.<br>
<br>
Explain to me why my Resistant/Neutral armor is less effective at mitigating damage from a Zerker than a Healer's Vulnerable armor is at mitigating the damage I do? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#000000>(6/2/03 11:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Real RvR damage vs. Damage Caps?</span><hr size=1> Because their style growth rates are 2-3x higher than yours live server. That is why.<br>
<br>
Even though dmg caps don't indicate normal dmg vs good resist + armor. If your style growth rate is 2-3x higher than you are gonna hit a lot harder. That does not mean they are hitting near their cap anymore than you are.<br>
<br>
The 10-20% dmg reduction coming from resists and higher af armor is overwhelmed by 100% more style dmg compared to other style lines.<br>
<br>
To give you an idea on how high the dmg. caps are for LA live. A shadowzerk has similar and slightly higher dmg. caps (depending on style) than a BM/Merc styled. And a berserker dmg caps are as high as 2H/Polearm (at same speeds, not if you compare at 5.5spd).<br>
<br>
I have logs of dmg cap with a 4.3spd 2Hander, they are similar (and some styles lower) to LA even though 2Handers get 40% more base dmg.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A> at: 6/2/03 11:25:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kerrecsnowmane>Kerrec Snowmane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#000000>(6/2/03 12:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Theories and Reproduceable Proof.</span><hr size=1> Ok, I'll buy that theory.  I personally haven't figured out any other reason that explains it.  Heck, I usually spend my time trying to argue the fact that Berserkers feel less of an effect from Armor Types than other fighters.<br>
<br>
However, to get Berserkers and other people to buy this, there has to be some way to test it, much the same as the Growth Rates, that shows the relation between Style Growth Rate and Armor Factor.  Unless that kind of proof is provided, no one will ever buy into it 100%.<br>
<br>
And before anyone points it out, I know that Berserkers hit Plate Armor for much less than Cloth.  However, many Berserkers I've argued with will not even acknowledge or discuss the fact that they'll hit Leather, Studded, Chain for nearly as much as Cloth, and suddenly see a drop in damage only against Plate.<br>
<br>
***ASIDE***<br>
<br>
Anyone  else notice these kinds of trends?  Evade is one such instance.  Take low level evade, and compare it unbuffed vs buffed.  Little difference.  Take the next level, compare and there's little difference.  Then suddenly, you hit a &quot;magic&quot; level of evade, where when you buff it, BoOM!...huge impact.  <br>
<br>
There's the Armor Factor with relation to Berserkers (and probably all other fighters to a lesser extent).  <br>
<br>
There is Weaponskill...anyone notice the huge difference 1800+ weaponskill makes?<br>
<br>
